In Godot Engine 3.x, you can create a first-person controller script for a KinematicBody node as follows:

```gdscript
extends KinematicBody

var speed = 20

func _physics_process(delta):
    var move_input = Vector2()
    if Input.is_action_pressed('ui_right'):
        move_input.x += 1
    if Input.is_action_pressed('ui_left'):
        move_input.x -= 1
    if Input.is_action_pressed('ui_down'):
        move_input.y += 1
    if Input.is_action_pressed('ui_up'):
        move_input.y -= 1
    move_input = move_input.normalized() * speed
    move_and_slide(move_input)
```

In Godot Engine 4.x, the KinematicBody node has been replaced with the RigidBody node. To create a first-person controller script for a RigidBody node, you can use the following code:

```gdscript
extends RigidBody

var speed = 20

func _physics_process(delta):
    var move_input = Vector2()
    if Input.is_action_pressed('ui_right'):
        move_input.x += 1
    if Input.is_action_pressed('ui_left'):
        move_input.x -= 1
    if Input.is_action_pressed('ui_down'):
        move_input.y += 1
    if Input.is_action_pressed('ui_up'):
        move_input.y -= 1
    move_input = move_input.normalized() * speed
    translate(move_input.x, 0, move_input.y)
```

